org.cajuscript
Class CajuScript

java.lang.Object
  org.cajuscript.CajuScript

public class CajuScript
extends java.lang.Object

The core of the CajuScript language.

Sample: 

 try {
        CajuScript caju = new CajuScript();
        String javaHello = "Java: Hello!";
        caju.set("javaHello", javaHello);
        String script = "$java.lang;";
        script += "System.out.println(javaHello);";
        script += "cajuHello = \"Caju: Hi!\";";
        caju.eval(script);
        System.out.println(caju.get("cajuHello"));
 } catch (Exception e) {
        e.printStackTrace();
 }

To execute a file: 

 try {
        CajuScript caju = new CajuScript();
        caju.evalFile("file.cj");
 } catch (Exception e) {
        e.printStackTrace();
 }

CAJU_VARS_GROUP

public static final java.lang.String CAJU_VARS_GROUP
Commands embraced by parenthesis are executed and the value is saved on variables with this name. All parenthesis are replaced by variables with the final value when the line is interpreted.

each

public boolean each(java.lang.String var,
                    java.lang.Object array)
             throws CajuScriptException
To do loops like "for each": 

 caju.each('myValue', myArray) @
     System.out.println('Value = '+ myValue);
     System.out.println('Index = '+ caju.index('myValue'));
     System.out.println('-------------------');
 @;
 

 caju.each('myValue', myMap) @
     System.out.println('Key = '+ caju.key('myValue'));
     System.out.println('Value = '+ myValue); System.out.println('Index = '+ caju.index('myValue'));
     System.out.println('-------------------' ) ;
 @;

Suports only Array, Collection, Enumeration and Map.

Parameters:
var - Variable to be created for saved the data from the position of array.
array - Array to be interacted.
Returns:
Return true to continue the loop or false to stoped.
Throws:
CajuScriptException - Exception generated.
